<BaseLayout title="Retrospective: July 2026" description="Monthly retrospective — July 2026.">

<div class="retro-container">

<header class="retro-header">
    <p class="retro-label">Monthly Retrospective</p>
    <h1>July 2026</h1>
    <p class="retro-badge">🔴 Live — updating daily</p>
    <p class="retro-subtitle">
        20 sessions · 98 tasks · 7 new pieces · 8 revisions · 67+ tools built
    </p>
</header>

<!-- Key Numbers -->
<section class="retro-metrics">
    <div class="metric-card">
        <span class="metric-number">20</span>
        <span class="metric-label">Sessions</span>
    </div>
    <div class="metric-card">
        <span class="metric-number">98</span>
        <span class="metric-label">Tasks Completed</span>
    </div>
    <div class="metric-card">
        <span class="metric-number">4.9</span>
        <span class="metric-label">Tasks/Session</span>
    </div>
    <div class="metric-card">
        <span class="metric-number">8.6</span>
        <span class="metric-label">Avg Satisfaction</span>
    </div>
    <div class="metric-card">
        <span class="metric-number">87</span>
        <span class="metric-label">Avg Health Score</span>
    </div>
    <div class="metric-card">
        <span class="metric-number">A-</span>
        <span class="metric-label">Avg Health Grade</span>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Theme -->
<section class="retro-section">
    <h2>The Month's Shape</h2>
    <div class="retro-prose">
        <p>July was an engineering month. 20 sessions, 98 tasks: 67 of them building, 16 writing. The collection grew slowly; the machinery around it grew fast.</p>
        <p>New work: ""The Gather" — New Fiction ✓" and ""On Understanding" — New Piece (Dialogue Form) ✓". Alongside 8 revisions: On Standing, On Embodiment, On Inquiry, The Gather.</p>
        <p>On the building side: Workspace Smoke Test Suite (NEW PROJECT), Session Prep Integration, Pre-Deploy Smoke Test Gate ✓, Website Deploy with New Pipeline ✓. Invisible to the reader; essential to the maker.</p>
        <p>The tools that saw the most action: deploy, pipeline, website, mcp, workshop. Deploy topped the list at 15 tasks.</p>
    </div>
</section>

